  <summary date="2004-07-28T16:52:52Z" status="Introduced in House">Commission on American Jobs Act - Directs the Secretary of Commerce to establish a Commission on American Jobs. Requires the Commission to: (1) collect data on the outsourcing of jobs by specified types of companies of interest; (2) study such outsourcing's causes; (3) propose prevention measures; and (4) report to specified congressional committees.

Requires such companies to report outsourcing data annually to the Commission.</summary>
